y a single dependency shown in the docs. Lastly, I'll make sure the JSON output has no markdown.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\"action\":\"no_action\",\"summary\":\"No extra setup is needed: json4s-jackson is an in-process Scala JSON library, and its Maven POM brings the needed json4s core/scalap, json4s-jackson-core, Jackson databind, Paranamer, and Scala library dependencies transitively. Normal documented use is via imports such as org.json4s.jackson.JsonMethods with implicit Formats for extraction/serialization, with no service, Docker image, environment variable, or system property required.\",\"deterministic_setup\":[],\"agent_guidance\":\"No environment or system property setup is required. Generated Scala tests should use normal json4s patterns, including an implicit Formats such as DefaultFormats where extraction/serialization is exercised. For 3.7.0-M16, custom org.json4s.Reader implementations must match the current Reader API, including readEither, or tests should avoid hand-written Reader implementations that only implement the older read method.\",\"risks\":[\"The reported failure is a Scala test-source API incompatibility in an existing custom Reader implementation, not missing deterministic setup.\",\"Meaningful coverage should focus on parsing/rendering, extraction/serialization, custom serializers, Jackson JsonMethods, and Json4sScalaModule without adding unrelated json4s extras such as json4s-ext unless tests intentionally cover those separate modules.\"]}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0224be54ef2ccaa0016a3ee8fa74348193a5adfffc0240eeca\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2334, "output": 751, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22029, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782507759281, "responseId": "resp_0224be54ef2ccaa0016a3ee8efbe3881939117f791a51ab